cs.DB, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with optimizing physical data storage and retrieval in databases, which is a core problem in database management systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a language for expressing physical database layouts and uses deductive synthesis to optimize queries, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses experiments conducted using a popular database benchmark, which indicates that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
